'No one ever called us': Retired French police officer stunned to learn of daughter's death online, three months after burial
subhed: Jean Forest discovered this summer that his daughter Marjolaine, a university scholar, had been buried in the spring. He investigated why his family was not informed and denounces the administrative and social indifference he encountered.

title: London's 'mudlarks' scour the Thames for treasure
subhed: On the banks of the British capital's river, London's 'mudlarks' search for fragments of the past: ancient pottery, old coins, bone dice. These enthusiasts are less motivated by the value of the objects than by the stories they tell. Sometimes, their finds even end up in a museum, as is currently being shown in an exhibition at the London Museum.
